                      <span>2</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-06-27</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>As a close follower of space exploration, I have read many of the biographies/autobiographies of the astronauts of the early space program and greatly enjoyed this book. In a review on this site, George S. Williams claimed it was poorly written and riddled with inaccuracies. Like other forms of writing, an editorial should provide support of your claim, so, Mr. Williams, I would appreciate if you could share with me and others specific aspects of the book that displeased you (I am more interested in falsities of the book than your disliking of the author's style). Please post a response on this website or email me at sbd218@nyu.edu</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">The missing link in astro biographies</div>
